{
  "stem": "27509.2",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then, before we knew, they went away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I was 20, and the youngest one was 12.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they were sent to Siberia.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "By the time they came back, we hardly knew one another, because the intervening war years-- we had different experiences, you see.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was a different background altogether.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The home as we knew it, and the rules, and the concepts that governed our life all went out through the window.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, yes, well, I had-- I have managed too, and I use the word managed advisedly, to graduate from gymnasium [? matric, ?] even though I was taken out the year 11 for a half a year, on Father's request, for economic reasons of this business, and again in year 12 for part of the first thought third of the year.",
      "word_count": 61
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I've-- despite of all that, I have done my [? matric ?] reasonably well and subsequently went forward to Warsaw, to the university in Warsaw, which was not a simple matter, because in the pre-war Poland, universities-- well, certain faculties were totally closed to Jewish students.",
      "word_count": 46
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You couldn't get in medicine.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You couldn't get in law.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You couldn't get in on many of those.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The only-- the only chance that we had at all was to go to the arts faculty, because that was not considered to be, in terms of economic potential, of any particular value, and just to-- most probably not to-- not to have a reputation in the international community that the [INAUDIBLE] is applicable totally to-- [INAUDIBLE] entire university.",
      "word_count": 59
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were let in on the-- in the faculty of arts.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But one-- a major aspect of it has to be accentuated and recorded.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "When I picked up my index-- because every student in Europe has an index.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
